===Estimate for &quot;Fb&quot;(&quot;n&quot;) and Σ(&quot;b&quot;)===
Let formula_1 be the number of digits. The function formula_14 determines the number of polydivisible numbers that has formula_1 digits in base formula_12, and the function formula_17 is the total number of polydivisible numbers in base formula_12.

If formula_19 is a polydivisible number in base formula_12 with formula_21 digits, then it can be extended to create a polydivisible number with formula_1 digits if there is a number between formula_23 and formula_24 that is divisible by formula_1. If formula_1 is less or equal to formula_12, then it is always possible to extend an formula_21 digit polydivisible number to an formula_1-digit polydivisible number in this way, and indeed there may be more than one possible extension. If formula_1 is greater than formula_12, it is not always possible to extend a polydivisible number in this way, and as formula_1 becomes larger, the chances of being able to extend a given polydivisible number become smaller. On average, each polydivisible number with formula_21 digits can be extended to a polydivisible number with formula_1 digits in formula_35 different ways. This leads to the following estimate for formula_36:

